cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for multi-label prediction in time-series data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Given that the proposed approach involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in deep learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for classification, which is covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for prediction also falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed approach for human activity recognition, which is a common application of computer vision, covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the problem of class imbalance, which is a common issue in machine learning and is covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
